{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643836","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643836"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:58:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:58:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18017"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18017","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18017"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10731"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78467"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10731"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18017"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63829"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7166"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24976"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24981"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78467"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is innervated by the posterior rami of cervical spinal nerves?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Posterior scalene","Sternocleidomastoid","Longus coli","Longus capitus","Splenius"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esplenius\u003C/strong\u003E group of muscles (including splenius capitis and cervicis) belongs to the intrinsic back muscles. These receive innervation from posterior rami of cervical spinal nerves and function to extend and rotate the head and neck.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn contrast:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior scalene\u003C/strong\u003E receives innervation from anterior rami of cervical nerves and functions to elevate rib two and flex the neck laterally\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esternocleidomastoid\u003C/strong\u003E has dual innervation from both the accessory nerve (CN XI) and anterior rami of cervical nerves, enabling head rotation and flexion\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elongus coli\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Elongus capitus\u003C/strong\u003E are prevertebral muscles innervated by anterior rami of cervical nerves that flex the cervical spine\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis pattern of innervation reflects the embryological development of these muscle groups, with intrinsic back muscles receiving posterior rami innervation while other neck muscles are supplied by anterior rami.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The posterior rami of cervical spinal nerves innervate the intrinsic muscles of the back, such as the splenius muscles.","The posterior scalene, longus coli, and longus capitus are innervated by the anterior rami of cervical spinal nerves."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2024). Tex